{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Philadelphia Crime Data Example\n",
    "## Reading the Data\n",
    "Below we load in a data set of crimes incidents in the Philadelphia area and the divide the sets into all crime events and theft crime events. Using pyscan we can then extract approximate regions of interest at scale."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pyscan\n",
    "import csv\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import random\n",
    "\n",
    "def get_coord(i, lst):\n",
    "    return [pt[i] for pt in lst]\n",
    "\n",
    "query = \"assault\"\n",
    "\n",
    "baseline = []\n",
    "measured = []\n",
    "with open(\"police_inct.csv\", \"r\") as f:\n",
    "    reader = csv.DictReader(f)\n",
    "    numAnomalies = 0\n",
    "    for row in reader:\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            x = float(row[\"POINT_X\"])\n",
    "            y = float(row[\"POINT_Y\"])\n",
    "            if not (39.8 < y < 40.2 and -76 < x):\n",
    "                continue\n",
    "        except:\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "            \n",
    "        point = pyscan.WPoint(1.0, x, y, 1.0)\n",
    "        baseline.append(point)\n",
    "        if \"theft\" in row[\"TEXT_GENERAL_CODE\"].lower():\n",
    "            measured.append(point)\n",
    "            "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can plot the data set to see the distribution of the theft vs. the background crime. In the below example we shuffle the points so that measured points or baseline points are systematically drawn over."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x7f5dd13faf28>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mixed_pts = list(zip(measured, [\"r\"] * len(measured))) + list(zip(baseline, [\"b\"] * len(baseline)))\n",
    "random.shuffle(mixed_pts)\n",
    "xs = get_coord(0, [p[0] for p in mixed_pts])\n",
    "ys = get_coord(1, [p[0] for p in mixed_pts])\n",
    "cs = [p[1] for p in mixed_pts]\n",
    "plt.scatter(xs, ys, color=cs, marker='.')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Subsampling \n",
    "It easy to use pyscan to extract an interesting region. The first step in most of the default scanning algorithms is contructing a \"net\" of points to define the regions of interest. This net can be created by taking a sample of the measured points and a sample of the baseline points and unioning them."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x7f5df00a2400>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "net = pyscan.my_sample(measured, 100) + pyscan.my_sample(baseline, 100)\n",
    "plt.scatter(get_coord(0, net), get_coord(1, net), marker='.')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We also take a sample of the measured points and a sample of the baseline points. A good rule of thumb is that your measured and baseline samples should be roughly 1/4 * len(net)^2, so in this example the sample sizes should be 5000."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x7f5dd1df3278>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#take the samples\n",
    "m_sample = pyscan.my_sample(measured, 5000) \n",
    "b_sample = pyscan.my_sample(baseline, 5000)\n",
    "\n",
    "#plot the samples\n",
    "mixed_samples = list(zip(m_sample, [\"r\"] * len(m_sample))) + list(zip(b_sample, [\"b\"] * len(b_sample)))\n",
    "random.shuffle(mixed_samples)\n",
    "xs = get_coord(0, [p[0] for p in mixed_samples])\n",
    "ys = get_coord(1, [p[0] for p in mixed_samples])\n",
    "cs = [p[1] for p in mixed_samples]\n",
    "plt.scatter(xs, ys, color=cs, marker='.')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Using the combination of the net and sample we can scan the point set using one of the various pyscan scanning functions.\n",
    "## Halfplane Scanning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x7f5dc9634c88>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "disc_f = pyscan.RKULLDORF\n",
    "halfplane, h_val = pyscan.max_halfplane(net, m_sample, b_sample, disc_f)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot halfplane\n",
    "l = halfplane.get_coords()\n",
    "# l = (a, b, c) where ax + by + c = 0 => (-ax -c) / b = y\n",
    "def f(x):\n",
    "    return -(x * l[0] + l[2]) / l[1]\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.scatter(xs, ys, color=cs, marker='.')\n",
    "plt.plot([-75.3, -74.95], [f(-75.2), f(-74.95)])\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Disk Scanning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x7f5dc9668278>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "disk, d_val = pyscan.max_disk(net, m_sample, b_sample, disc_f)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot disk\n",
    "ax = plt.subplot()\n",
    "ax.scatter(xs, ys, color=cs, marker='.')\n",
    "d = plt.Circle(disk.get_origin(), disk.get_radius(), color='g', alpha=.8)\n",
    "ax.add_artist(d)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Rectangle Scanning\n",
    "Rectangle scanning by default doesn't use a point \"net\" though it is possible to use a net if needed."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x7f5dc9626320>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# all of these methods create a grid first and then scan the grid using various methods.\n",
    "grid = pyscan.Grid(100, m_sample, b_sample)\n",
    "\n",
    "# a slow exact method \n",
    "subgrid = pyscan.max_subgrid(grid, disc_f)\n",
    "rect = grid.toRectangle(subgrid)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax = plt.subplot()\n",
    "ax.scatter(xs, ys, color=cs, marker='.')\n",
    "r = plt.Rectangle((rect.lowX(), rect.lowY()), rect.upX() - rect.lowX(), rect.upY() - rect.lowY(), \n",
    "                  alpha=.8, \n",
    "                  color='g')\n",
    "ax.add_artist(r)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x7f5dc9634748>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# a faster approximate method \n",
    "subgrid = pyscan.max_subgrid_convex(grid, .01, disc_f)\n",
    "rect = grid.toRectangle(subgrid)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax = plt.subplot()\n",
    "ax.scatter(xs, ys, color=cs, marker='.')\n",
    "r = plt.Rectangle((rect.lowX(), rect.lowY()), rect.upX() - rect.lowX(), rect.upY() - rect.lowY(), \n",
    "                  alpha=.8, \n",
    "                  color='g')\n",
    "ax.add_artist(r)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
 ],
